âš–ï¸ Workflow

1. Collect features (X)


2. Collect labels (y)


3. Train the model with X and y



ğŸ–‹ï¸ Sample Code (scikit-learn)

import numpy as np
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Features (house size, distance from station)
X = np.array([[30, 10], [50, 8], [70, 5]])  # size(mÂ²), distance(km)
# Labels (house price)
y = np.array([300, 500, 700])               # price in thousands

# Train model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X, y)

# Predict
print(model.predict([[60, 6]]))  # 60mÂ², 6km from station

